<subsection xml:id="lec-representarNumDeDistintasManeras" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">

<shorttitle>Lección 1 </shorttitle>
<title>Lección 1 -<nbsp/></title>
<title>Representemos números de distintas maneras</title>


<!-- ============================================ 
  Objetivos de aprendizaje                        
=================================================  -->

<!-- Frase resumen para estudiante. Originalmente [Student Facing Goals] -->
<introduction component="est-goal"> 
  <p>Representemos números de distintas maneras.</p>
</introduction>

<!-- Objetivos para el estudiante. Originalmente [Student-Facing Targets] -->
<!-- <objectives component="estudiante">
  <ul>
    <li>[@@@@@@@@@@@@@@]</li>
  </ul>
</objectives> -->

<!-- Objetivos que solo ve el profesor. Originalmente [Teacher Facing Goals] -->
<objectives component="profesor">
  <ul>
    <li><p>[+++++++++++++++++]</p></li>
    <li><p>Represent numbers to 1,000 in different ways using place value understanding.</p></li>
  </ul>
</objectives>


<!-- ============================================ 
  Introducción para el profesor                        
=================================================  -->
<introduction component="profesor">

  <!-- Estándares CCSS asociados -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="ccss-leccion-titulo"/></title> 
    <ul>      
      <li>
        <custom ref="ccss-buildingOn"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-2-NBT-A-1" text="custom">2.NBT.A.1</xref>,
        <xref ref="ccss-2-NBT-A-3" text="custom">2.NBT.A.3</xref>
      </li>
      <li>
        <custom ref="ccss-buildingTowards"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-2-NBT-A-2" text="custom">2.NBT.A.2</xref>
      </li>
    </ul>
    </paragraphs>

  <!-- índice de la lección (automático) -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="timeline-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <list-of elements="subsubsection reading-questions" scope="subsection"/>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Propósito de la lección -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="purpose-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this lesson is for students to represent numbers using base-ten blocks, base-ten diagrams, expanded form, numerals, and word form.</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Materiales requeridos -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="materials-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>Actividad 1</p>
        <xi:include href="./act-clasificacionDeTarjetas-numsEnSusDiferentesFormas-mat.ptx"/>
        <!--<xi:include href="./act-clasificacionDeTarjetas-numsEnSusDiferentesFormas-matCentros.ptx"/>-->
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Actividad 2</p>
        <xi:include href="./act-mesaRedondaDeNumEnDistintasFormas-mat.ptx"/>
        <!--<xi:include href="./act-mesaRedondaDeNumEnDistintasFormas-matCentros.ptx"/>-->
      </li>
    </ul> 
  </paragraphs>
  
  <!-- Introducción de la lección (narrative) -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Prior to this grade, students represented numbers within 1,000 using number names, base-ten blocks and diagrams, and expanded form. They used place value to compose and decompose numbers within 1,000.</p>
    <p>In this lesson, students revisit these familiar representations and ways of reasoning about numbers as they work to build fluency with addition and subtraction within 1,000. The base-ten diagrams and the expanded form will continue to be used to support students throughout this unit. Give students access to base-ten blocks, in case requested.</p>
  </paragraphs>
  
  <!-- Preguntas de reflexión profesor -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="reflection-quest-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Whose ideas were shared in class today? How can you leverage each of your students’ ideas to support them in being seen and heard in tomorrow’s math class?</p>
  </paragraphs>
</introduction>


